#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:50 b5b831b457c44495a34dae8c7ac87579
msgid ""
"Blank issues are disabled — every issue starts from a template, which "
"keeps triage tractable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:55 f084f634708d4e22ba14401c1c57db5f
msgid "What each template captures"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:57 58b025309d4c4e278d378ae47a53a6f5
msgid ""
"Both templates are GitHub *issue forms*: structured fields with "
"validation, rendered as a form rather than free-form Markdown. Required "
"fields are clearly marked."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:61 de6da06eb8a9491295cf50c30bdc50b2
msgid ""
"**🐛 Bug Report** — required fields are *Description*, *Minimal "
"reproducing example*, *Expected behavior*, *Environment*, plus two pre-"
"flight checkboxes. The full traceback is optional (some bugs produce a "
"wrong result rather than an exception). The environment field tells you "
"exactly what to paste:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:77 f8474e356c5a411bb36c7db15f475c01
msgid ""
"If you can't fill out the *Minimal reproducing example*, that usually "
"means the problem isn't reduced enough yet — try to shrink it before "
"filing. A 200-line script and a five-line script take roughly the same "
"amount of human attention to read, and the five-line script is ten times "
"more likely to get a fast answer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:83 647d1a69f5c545c2aed81d24369d79a7
msgid ""
"**✨ Feature Request** — only *Use case* is strictly required. Lead with "
"the **motivation** (\"I'm trying to solve X\") rather than a proposed API"
" (\"please add ``foo``\"). A clear use case lets the maintainers and the "
"community shape the API together; a pre-specified API often anchors the "
"discussion in the wrong place."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:91 7470c052039a4d2993158730fa31c6c1
msgid "What happens after you file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:93 2f1723c2de4443a3844483908cad31ea
msgid "The basic shape:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:95 d31bd735db314afbbf8af6e30772215d
msgid ""
"**Auto-label** — every new issue lands with the ``triage`` label plus its"
" category (``bug`` or ``enhancement``), set by the template."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:98 658b0e8d30dc4d9f869d0ec237b152a6
msgid ""
"**Triage** — a maintainer reads it, possibly asks for more info, removes "
"``triage`` once the report is actionable, and adds topic labels (e.g. "
"``meshing``, ``solver``, ``cuda``) so similar issues cluster together."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:102
#: 021a755eada2486cb4e87eafb68bf68e
msgid "**Disposition** — one of:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:104
#: f3f8a4b828ee41e0a5f270794e62cd65
msgid ""
"Confirmed and queued for work (someone will pick it up; you are welcome "
"to too — see :doc:`contributing`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:106
#: b3d60261f9b04716aaa93ae32a57fc17
msgid ""
"Asked for clarification (please respond; stale issues with no follow-up "
"may be closed)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:108
#: abbbc69b4e7d4a2580524bce97f359f5
msgid "Closed as a duplicate, invalid, or \"won't fix\" with an explanation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:111
#: 8ae113394b4a46df921d14e9bac8e5bc
msgid ""
"This is a research-affiliated project with a small maintainer team — "
"response times are best-effort, not contractual. If your issue is urgent "
"for a paper deadline, mention it in the description; if it has been "
"silent for more than two weeks, a polite ping is welcome."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:118
#: 517116e1b197464fa6a7747a2a92a08a
msgid "Before you file: search first"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:120
#: 6022d56022154a66a928a4e497652811
msgid ""
"A 30-second search avoids most duplicates and often turns up an existing "
"workaround. Useful entry points:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:123
#: 89e2eba767dc425787272a807e809f1e
msgid ""
"Open + closed issues, scoped to this repo: ``https://github.com/camlab-"
"ethz/TensorMesh/issues?q=<terms>`` (drop the default ``is:open`` to "
"include closed ones)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:126
#: a40bcc53971e4be19fd9286345d55a62
msgid ""
"Discussions — usage questions and design conversations live there, not "
"here."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:128
#: 0decdc7621e64d79a6e4fd894ecbb199
msgid ""
"Google with a ``site:`` filter: ``site:github.com/camlab-ethz/TensorMesh "
"<your terms>``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:131
#: 4b4a063d4518426eaf851322c61d4a79
msgid ""
"If you find a related issue but yours is genuinely different, link to it "
"from your new issue (\"related to #NN, but X is different\") — that helps"
" triage decide whether to merge them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:137
#: 3f87cdf960ca4eeea0bc0b77ffde4908
msgid "From Discussion to Issue"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:139
#: 162decf689e04b56bea7c768622bfe8c
msgid "Issues and Discussions cross over in two natural directions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:141
#: c67f84595b2c46dc8413bd4e053ee72c
msgid ""
"**Q&A → Bug.** A \"how do I…\" question on Discussions Q&A turns out to "
"be a real bug. Open an issue, reference the discussion thread for context"
" (``Discussion: #DD``), and link the issue back from the discussion. "
"Don't re-paste the whole transcript."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:145
#: 6d64b990504443f19ab91c26c7f46e65
msgid ""
"**Idea & RFC → Feature.** After a design discussion converges, file an "
"issue (or a PR) with the agreed design in the description, and link the "
"discussion thread. The issue is then the *commitment*; the discussion is "
"the *deliberation*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:152
#: fc8aa62d3b7247fa846a700845ea9c11
msgid "Pull requests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:154
#: b184f312fd894ccd972dd697e458ecfa
msgid ""
"This page is about *filing* issues. If you want to *fix* one, the PR "
"workflow — dev environment, branch naming, tests, doc updates — lives in "
":doc:`contributing`. Linking the PR to its issue (``Fixes #NN`` in the "
"description) auto-closes the issue on merge, which the triage flow above "
"relies on."
msgstr ""

